size_t

modern, lvl.1.4/1.5

unsigned integer type defined in [stddefh.] (not a keyword of the language)
represents values in the range [0, SIZE_MAX] (1)
    - SIZE_MAX defined in [stdint.h]
    - for sizes, cardinalities, etc.
type-operator sizeof returns int of type size_t (2)

printf()-specifier: %zu

EXAMPLE
(1)
printf("%zu", SIZE_MAX); // 18446744073709551615 == 2^64 - 1
(2)
char a[3];
printf("%zu\n", sizeof a); // 3
